rce to "save socialism" to contemplation of the end of the cold war, here is a far more candid picture of Gorbachev than we have ever seen before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPerestroĭka. 0aPerestroĭka. 0aSocialism. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Archie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Archie.1 aGorbachev, Mikhail.1 aMlynar, Zdenek, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aShriver, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShriver, George.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/gorb1186440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231505055423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231505055/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK